				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">We can still sell them anyway - we just have to cast them as we go.
<br />

<br />
This issue is one of those things that has been irking me about being a mage. Its so frustrating that I can't precast all the gear we know we will need, I have to wait until everyone is there and ready to accept the items.
<br />

<br />
It would be great to be able to cast the items ahead of time. Keep them no-rent, that is fine but I also don't see a good reason for them to be lore, except the frustration factor that i have to give away my own piece and then recast it. Also, when you cast this nice gear, you are the only one who can't be wearing it as you cast it. It doesn't make much sense.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
