			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Although I really like the idea of the summoned items being changed to rentable, I think its a big departure from what we currently have. If it was changed to that, I would not complain at all!  But, I also believe that asking for too much can sometimes end up giving you nothing.
<br />

<br />
The easiest solution (the one least likely to "unbalance" the intention of the items, or create some sort of exploit) might be to target summon. I can live with that.
<br />

<br />
Or, to remove the lore status, that would be very handy without any serious repercussions that I can think of, except that all of my pets would wear that gear since I would make it in the down time (ie outside of the LDoN dungeons instead of waiting until the pets are cast inside).
<br />

<br />
Having them rentable is nice, but then I think I would never have any real startup time, except for Xev bags. And those should never be rentable, otherwise we just flooded the market with the best bags out there and with no negative factor.
<br />

<br />
I like the items we cast to be consistent.  All non-lore, rentable would be fine, but a long way from what we have.  I can live with non-lore no-rent just fine though <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
